The paper proposes an algorithm for large-scale anomaly detection, which is a common problem in machine learning and data science. The algorithm is based on kernel methods and stochastic optimization, which are both popular topics in the CS community. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions the linear computational complexity and the stochastic gradient descent algorithm, which are related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory), respectively.
